From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Proton GE Team <proton-ge@example.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 05:20:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winedmo: Pace DirectShow video transform draining.

Arcania's new-game intro can produce decoded 1280x720 RGB frames faster
than the renderer consumes them.  Yield after one delivered video frame during
normal Receive() flow, keep full draining for explicit EOS, and avoid
decoding unselected ASF audio streams so downstream backpressure can pace
decode before the graph exhausts 32-bit address space with queued RGB frames.
